<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-084-180 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 107 797</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  August 8 1991* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Borland assumes 51% ownership of its Japanese subsidiary. (BorlandInternational Inc., Borland Japan)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Miyazawa, Masayuki.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Borland International Inc. (Investments)Borland Japan (Management).andO;Ticker:    BORL.andO;Topic:     InvestmentsSubsidiary CompaniesManagement StyleJapan.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>BORLAND ASSUMES 51% OWNERSHIP OF ITS JAPANESE SUBSIDIARY 08/08/91 TOKYO,JAPAN, 1991 AUG 8 (NB) -- Borland International has gained 51 percent of theequity in its Japanese subsidiary Borland Japan.andM;The 30 million yen ($222,000) share of Borland Japan was previously owned byTokyo-based software firm Microsoft Associates.andP;  Borland, which bought theshares, now holds an estimated 147 million yen investment ($1 million USdollars) with its 51 percent share.andM;Borland has also sent a company director, Fumito Hara, to the Japanesesubsidiary to assume management responsibilities.andP;  He is known as a venturecapitalist and has invested in Authorware and other firms, according to theNikkei Personal Computing magazine.andP;  He is expected to combine both Americanand Japanese techniques of sales and the management in Japan.andM;Borland International is seeking a larger share of the Japanese softwaremarket.andP;  The first move will be to develop a Japanese version of Paradox forWindows 3.0., with other products following suit.andM;(Masayuki Miyazawa/19910805/Press Contact: Microsoftware Associates,andplus;81-3-3486-1411)</TEXT></DOC>